-serif; font-size:14px; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:17px; text-decoration:none;" target="_blank">Tamsin Embleton (@tamsinembleton) 分享的帖子</a></p></div></blockquote><p><script async src="//platform.instagram.com/en_US/embeds.js"></script></p><p> Tamsin Embleton 是一位心理治疗师和前巡演预订员，也是广受好评的<em>《巡演与心理健康：音乐产业手册》</em>一书的作者，这本 600 页的书提供了“音乐家巡演指南将帮助艺术家、巡演经理、制作人”经理、工作人员和艺术家团队识别并应对巡演期间或巡演期间可能出现的各种心理困难”。</p><p>这本书与心理治疗师、表演和声乐教练、营养师、心理学家以及睡眠、性健康和成瘾专家一起撰写，采访了<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/nile-rogers">Nile Rogers</a> 、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/artiss/four-tet">Four Tet</a> 、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/radiohead">Radiohead 的</a><a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/philip-selway">Philip Selway</a>等人，同时提供了“实用指导、资源、心理教育”等内容，为业内人士寻找最佳方式处理旅途生活而不会遭受倦怠、焦虑或抑郁的内容。</p><p> “这是一个吸引相当复杂、有趣、古怪的人的行业；他们中的许多人都在幕后努力解决问题，”恩布尔顿告诉<em>《NME》</em> 。 “我派了很多艺术家去巡演，我日复一日地在场馆工作。巡演真的很紧张，有点像高压锅。在表面之下，你已经在挣扎的事情将会加剧​​。你没有个人空间，这会在生理、心理和社交上对你造成打击。”</p><p>恩布尔顿承认，“艺术家们还没有为巡演的现实做好准备”，他说：“他们对巡演的情况抱有一些梦想，所有令人兴奋的事情都是真实的，但那些高潮需要你的身体处理和恢复。你睡不好觉，大多数晚上都在吃派对食物，然后就有了丰富的物质，以及每场演出都需要成为派对的心态。”</p><p>在描述“每场演出都以酒精为标志”的本质时，恩布尔顿解释了酒精和物质如何“融入现场音乐文化”；总会“对你第二天的焦虑产生影响”的事情。</p><p> “我们讨论场馆如何为不喝酒或不想喝酒的人提供干燥更衣室和更好的选择，”她建议道。 “它具有所有这些次要影响，并且在路上形成了很多成瘾行为。只要你能做好你的工作，只要你在某一领域表现出色，那么其他方面往往就会被忽视。这是一种应对机制，但不是唯一的。</p><p> “艺术家往往对其环境中的事物更加反思和反应。我们需要他们这样才能创造，但这也可能使他们在某些高压力情况下更容易受到伤害。” </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="给音乐家的心理健康建议 - 理查德·朱普" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/k0fNSbOjpuU?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p>作者同意洛基的观点，即巡演可以变得更加容易，无需承担社交媒体的责任，也可以“重视音乐之外的关系”。</p><p> “音乐可以说是一站式商店，”恩布尔顿解释道。 “这显然是一个工作场所，而且关系通常是非正式的。你建立了很多友谊，但如果你离开这个行业或只是离开，你会很容易受到伤害。这通常是相当令人震惊的。</p><p>她继续说道：“当然，作为一名艺术家，还有非常现代的社交媒体方面——要么不断地处于显微镜下，要么感觉自己需要参与。这对于音乐行业来说可能是一个相当新的概念。媒体一直都有，但并不需要如此程度地分享你的每一天。”</p><p>恩布尔顿引用了 Pop Justice 的彼得·罗宾逊（Pop Justice 也是一名治疗师和媒体处理教练）在她的书中的一章，建议艺术家“要有界限，以便感觉与网络自我和真实自我分开”。</p><p> “你可以利用休息时间做什么？”她开始说道。 “不要通过社交媒体告诉人们这件事，否则这将成为内容。当你的生活变得满足时，这是一件非常扭曲的事情。它已经成为我们衡量当今所有事物的指标——流量、分享、点赞、数字和参与度。”</p><p>恩布尔顿补充说，虽然这场危机“需要解决”，但音乐最终是“一个压力很大的行业”，一个“动荡、不可预测”的行业，“会让你面临很多批评”，而且通常不愿意改变。</p><p> “这也会给你的人际关系带来挑战，因为你的工作是首要和中心，”她说。 “没有人教你如何驾驭它。该行业倾向于说，“让我们让这个人更有弹性，以便他们能够应对”，而不是说，“好吧，也许我们可以改变一些工作实践”。事实上，我们两者都需要。” </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="我是如何开始撰写《巡演与心理健康手册》的？塔姆辛·恩布尔顿" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/KMsHKiy5erA?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p>虽然巡演在日程安排的强度和对艺术家的期望方面仍然“不受监管”，但恩布尔顿表示，她希望她的书能够帮助那些管理巡演的人能够更好地驾驭这艘船，避免灾难。</p><p> “巡演就像坐过山车，我们必须帮助人们度过高潮和低谷，并了解身体的压力反应，”她说。 “我们谈论了很多关于节奏、能力和注意义务的问题。为了这本书，我采访了大约 80 个人，其中包括很多旅游经理。回想起来，他们中的很多人都想，‘我助长了一些成瘾’——包括性和色情成瘾，这在路上是相当大的——或者他们没有很好地应对压力。”</p><p>她接着说：“我和吉姆·迪格比（Jim Digby）交谈，他曾经负责<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/linkin-park">林肯公园（Linkin Park）的工作</a>，谈论他们如何应对<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/linkin-park-chester-benningtons-cause-death-confirmed-coroner-2115182#:~:text=Linkin%20Park%20frontman%20Chester%20Bennington's,a%20lengthy%20battle%20with%20depression.">查斯特·贝宁顿（Chester Bennington）自杀的后果</a>。他们设立了团体治疗课程：结果发现其他人有自杀倾向，所以他们能够为他们提供帮助。这表明我们如何在实用的同时帮助人们驾驭巡演和乐队的情感世界。”</p><p><a href="https://www.touringmanual.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">请访问此处</a>，了解有关<em>音乐和巡演的更多信息：音乐行业手册</em>。</p><p> While also pointing out the number of services that are now available to struggling musicians alongside her own therapy group ran alongside music industry professionals, Embleton said that she hoped the growing community voice would help spread awareness of better coping mechanisms, as well as advocating for better mental health in live music.</p><p> “We&#39;ve got really high rates of, addiction, suicide, anxiety and depression, in artists, crew, and touring people,” she said. “I&#39;ve had so many people around the world say to me, &#39;We&#39;ve needed this – I wish I had this 20 years ago&#39;. Hopefully we&#39;re going to help a lot people recognise early warning signs and get people help and slow down a little bit.”</p><h2> <strong>For further help and advice on mental health:</strong></h2><ul><li> <a href="https://www.nme.com/blogs/am-i-depressed-how-to-tell-2067753" target="_blank" rel="noopener">&#39;Am I depressed?&#39; – Help and advice on mental health and what to do next</a></li><li> <a href="https://www.tonicmusic.co.uk/tonic-rider" target="_blank" rel="noopener">TONIC Rider – Bespoke training and support for music industry professionals</a></li><li> <a href="https://www.helpmusicians.org.uk/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Help Musicians UK – Around the clock mental health support and advice for musicians</a></li><li> <a href="https://www.musicsupport.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Music Support Org – Help and support for musicians struggling with alcoholism, addiction, or mental health issues</a></li><li> <a href="https://www.youngminds.org.uk/?gclid=CIuC-9ye69ICFQYo0wodX48KPA" target="_blank" rel="noopener">YOUNG MINDS – The voice for young people&#39;s health and wellbeing</a></li><li> <a href="https://www.thecalmzone.net/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">CALM – The Campaign Against Living Miserably</a></li><li> <a href="https://www.samaritans.org/how-we-can-help/contact-samaritan/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">The Samaritans – Confidential support 24 hours a day</a></li></ul><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/pressure-cooker-impact-of-touring-on-mental-health-needs-addressing-but-help-is-at-hand-3512555">“Pressure cooker” impact of touring on mental health “needs addressing” – but help is at hand</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
 Easy Life to surrender band name after “David and Goliath” legal battle with EasyJet and EasyGroup https://www.nme.com/news/music/easy-life-to-surrender-band-name-after-david-and-goliath-legal-battle-with-easyjet-and-easygroup-3512563?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=easy-life-to-surrender-band-name-after-david-and-goliath-legal-battle-with-easyjet-and-easygroupElizabeth Aubrey Tue, 10 Oct 2023 18:22:02 +0000 Music NewsNewsIndieLive Music News https://www.nme.com/?p=3512563 <p><img width="2000" height="1271" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Easy-life-performing-live.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="轻松生活" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Easy-life-performing-live.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Easy-life-performing-live-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Easy-life-performing-live-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Easy-life-performing-live-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Easy-life-performing-live-1392x885.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Easy-life-performing-live-1068x679.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> &quot;Sadly, it seems that justice is only available to those who can afford it. We simply don&#39;t have the funds to access a fair trial in the high court&quot;</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/easy-life-to-surrender-band-name-after-david-and-goliath-legal-battle-with-easyjet-and-easygroup-3512563">Easy Life to surrender band name after “David and Goliath” legal battle with EasyJet and EasyGroup</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1271" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Easy-life-performing-live.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="轻松生活" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Easy-life-performing-live.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Easy-life-performing-live-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Easy-life-performing-live-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Easy-life-performing-live-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Easy-life-performing-live-1392x885.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Easy-life-performing-live-1068x679.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/easy-life">Easy Life</a> have today (October 10) taken to social media to say that they&#39;re having to surrender their band name following a “David and Goliath” legal battle with EasyGroup.</p><ul class="post-content-read-more"><li> <strong>READ MORE: <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/murray-matravers-on-easy-lifes-rise-if-youre-enjoying-and-healthy-in-your-mind-that-for-me-is-succes-3489941">Murray Matravers on Easy Life&#39;s rise: “If you&#39;re enjoying it and you&#39;re healthy in your mind, that for me is success”</a></strong></li></ul><p> Earlier this week, the band revealed that they <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/easy-life-say-theyre-being-sued-by-easyjet-over-their-name-3507949">were being sued by the conglomerate</a> and claimed the company was “forcing” them to change their name or they risked facing a costly legal battle.</p><p> Easygroup are the Cayman Islands-registered company owned by Sir Stelios Haji-Ioannou built to expand the “easy” brand from EasyJet&#39;s airlines into the fields of hotels, supermarkets, financial services and more – licensing out the “easy” name.</p><p> Now, in a new post on the <a href="https://www.easylifemusic.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">website</a> , the band have updated fans to say that despite “having explored literally every possible angle,” the band have “realised that there are no good options available” and that they have to subsequently “change our name to move forward.”</p><p> In the statement, the band wrote: “Sadly, it seems that justice is only available to those who can afford it. We simply don&#39;t have the funds to access a fair trial in the high court. Not to mention the fact that this would likely rattle on through to 2025, and with this hanging over us we wouldn&#39;t be able to release any music in the meantime. Our careers, and indeed our lives, would be on hold.</p><p> “We&#39;re not a nameless company; as you&#39;ve seen, it&#39;s our own personal names on the paperwork. This means that should we lose, the costs will be recouped from us personally. They could take everything; material possessions, our livelihoods, our homes.”</p><p> The band went on to describe the “turmoil” the situation had caused them but that they&#39;d “found solace in the outpourings of love and support” from their fans.</p><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="550" data-dnt="true"><p lang="en" dir="ltr"> Sadly, we have realised that there are no good options available to us in the situation we find ourselves in. We have no power to fight this. I&#39;ve written a more detailed letter which I&#39;ll post on our site now that explains the legal side of what&#39;s going on a bit more</p><p> — easy life (@easylife) <a href="https://twitter.com/easylife/status/1711775078294159862?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">October 10, 2023</a> </p></blockquote><p><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></p><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="550" data-dnt="true"><p lang="en" dir="ltr"> but essentially it&#39;s David vs Goliath and our British legal system favours Goliath. Friday is to be our last day as easy life. Best believe we want to go out in style.</p><p> easy life, for the very last time. Tickets on sale now – only £15 each so come join us for a proper farewell.</p><p> — easy life (@easylife) <a href="https://twitter.com/easylife/status/1711775172623999437?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">October 10, 2023</a> </p></blockquote><p><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></p><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="550" data-dnt="true"><p lang="zxx" dir="ltr"> <a href="https://t.co/AJ2iQ8gTI3">https://t.co/AJ2iQ8gTI3</a> <a href="https://t.co/aD1Z8xP3kf">pic.twitter.com/aD1Z8xP3kf</a></p><p> — easy life (@easylife) <a href="https://twitter.com/easylife/status/1711775360994492659?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">October 10, 2023</a> </p></blockquote><p><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></p><p></p><p> This Friday (October 13), will be the final day the band will be using the name. They have organised some “farewell parties” for fans. The first will take place on Thursday October 12 at Leicester Academy, with the second following at Koko on Friday October 13. You can get tickets for the events <a href="https://easylife.lnk.to/verylasttime" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a> .</p><p> They added: “Even though we aren&#39;t able to fight this, we now need to go into a period of legal mediation with EasyGroup about what happens next. We&#39;re really hoping they might be gracious about this, and we are hopeful for the opportunity to finally put out the song we know you&#39;ve been wanting for years. Still not as we&#39;d imagined, but it&#39;s a song for you guys and we want you to have it.</p><p> “It&#39;s with the deepest sadness that I confirm once again, that we, as easy life, will be playing our final shows this week. Perhaps our case will help provoke a dialogue around legal reform and justice being available to all, however I fear such conversations will fall on deaf ears. Who knows what will happen next, every storm runs out of rain eventually.”</p><p> EasyGroup have not yet responded to the band&#39;s latest statement. However, in response to the band&#39;s original claim, an EasyGroup spokesperson told <em>NME</em> earlier this week: “Stelios and easyGroup founded and (now) own the right to the easy brand name.</p><p> “Other companies (including easyLife) pay annual royalties for its use as part of their business strategy. We cannot allow unauthorised third parties to simply use it free, gratis and for nothing. That would be very unfair.”</p><p> The company said in a <a href="https://easy.com/comment-from-easygroup-concerning-brand-theft-by-mr-matravers-and-others/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">separate statement</a> : “With reference to the brand thief Mr Matravers and his fellow band members who have decided to use our brand, easyLife, without permission, we have a long established record of legally stopping thieves from using our brands and I am confident we will stop Mr Matravers.” </p><figure id="attachment_3512571" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3512571" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3512571" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Easy-Life-Performing-Live-2.jpg" alt="轻松生活" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Easy-Life-Performing-Live-2.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Easy-Life-Performing-Live-2-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Easy-Life-Performing-Live-2-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Easy-Life-Performing-Live-2-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Easy-Life-Performing-Live-2-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Easy-Life-Performing-Live-2-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3512571" class="wp-caption-text"> Easy Life – CREDIT: Getty</figcaption></figure><p> The band <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/easy-life-hit-back-at-easygroup-calling-them-brand-thieves-arguing-they-came-first-3508618">refuted the suggestion that they were “brand thieves”</a> and argued that they had been using their name a long time before the conglomerate licensed the name of the online retailer EasyLife, for which it receives an annual fee. The owner of EasyGroup has no financial interest in the business.</p><p> Earlier this week, <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/easy-lifes-mp-makes-plea-to-easyjet-to-withdraw-legal-action-3511110">the band&#39;s MP, Harriet Harman made a plea to EasyGroup asking them to retract their threat of legal action against the band.</a></p><p> This isn&#39;t the first time EasyGroup have sued other businesses for using names containing the word &#39;easy&#39;. In 2018, the company took legal action against <a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/netflix">Netflix</a> over its comedy series Easy, claiming its use of the name breached its European trademarks.</p><p> In response, Netflix said in a statement that “viewers can tell the difference between a show they watch and a plane they fly in.” In 2008, the Northampton-based restaurant easyCurry also changed its name after being threatened with legal action.</p><p> The <em>NME</em> Award-winning band EasyLife have released two acclaimed albums – 2022&#39;s &#39; <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/easy-life-maybe-in-another-life-review-3319791">Maybe In Another Life</a> &#39; and 2021 debut &#39; <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/easy-life-lifes-a-beach-review-radar-2949766">Life&#39;s A Beach</a> &#39;. They have been active since 2017.</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/easy-life-to-surrender-band-name-after-david-and-goliath-legal-battle-with-easyjet-and-easygroup-3512563">Easy Life to surrender band name after “David and Goliath” legal battle with EasyJet and EasyGroup</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
